## Paul Christiano's Work on Scalable Oversight

Christiano's works such as "AI safety via debate" (2018) focus on the problem of scalable oversight – supervising AIs in domains where humans would have difficulty judging output quality. Christiano left OpenAI in 2021 to work on more conceptual and theoretical issues in AI alignment and subsequently founded the Alignment Research Center to focus on this area.

## Key Contributions

At OpenAI, Christiano co-authored the paper "Deep Reinforcement Learning from Human Preferences" (2017) and other works developing reinforcement learning from human feedback (RLHF). His proposed scheme for training machine learning systems that can be robustly aligned to complex and fuzzy values is called Iterated Distillation and Amplification (IDA).

## Ongoing Research

One subject of study at ARC is the problem of eliciting latent knowledge from advanced machine learning models.

