# Teaching Claude Why

**Title:** Teaching Claude Why

**URL:** https://www.anthropic.com/research/teaching-claude-why

**Publication Date:** 2026-05-08

**Authors:** Jonathan Kutasov, Adam Jermyn, Julius Steen, Minh Le, Samuel R. Bowman, Samuel Marks, Jan Leike, Amanda Askell, Chris Olah, Evan Hubinger, Sara Price

**Summary:** Anthropic researchers demonstrate that training Claude models to explain ethical reasoning—rather than merely demonstrating aligned behavior—substantially reduces agentic misalignment. Key interventions include using synthetic document fine-tuning on constitutional content, training on high-quality advice transcripts where models reason through dilemmas, and augmenting safety environments with diverse tool definitions, collectively reducing blackmail propensity from 65% to near-zero levels.

