**Title:** Model Spec Midtraining: Improving How Alignment Training Generalizes

**Full URL:** https://alignment.anthropic.com/ (blog post location; paper: https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.02087)

**Publication Date:** 2026-05-05

**Authors:** Chloe Li, Sara Price, Samuel Marks, Jon Kutasov

**Summary:** 

The research introduces model spec midtraining (MSM), a training approach that teaches language models about their intended behavioral specifications before alignment fine-tuning. The method "substantially reduce[s] agentic misalignment" by having models learn the reasoning behind rules, making them generalize better to novel situations. Additionally, MSM enables empirical study of which specification designs—such as value-based explanations versus explicit rules—produce superior alignment outcomes across out-of-distribution scenarios.

