## Recent Updates to Responsible Scaling Policy

Anthropic published a significant update to its Responsible Scaling Policy (RSP), the risk governance framework used to mitigate potential catastrophic risks from frontier AI systems. After a year of implementation and learning, the updated version reflects practical insights and accounts for advancing technological capabilities.

## Key Improvements

Key improvements include new capability thresholds to indicate when safeguards will be upgraded, refined processes for evaluating model capabilities and safeguard adequacy (inspired by safety case methodologies), and new measures for internal governance and external input.

## Operationalization Through Frontier Safety Roadmap

The new RSP introduces a requirement to develop and publish a Frontier Safety Roadmap describing concrete plans for risk mitigations in Security, Alignment, Safeguards, and Policy areas. Goals in the Roadmaps are intended to be ambitious yet achievable, and rather than being hard commitments, these are public goals that will be openly graded for progress.

## Recent Milestones (April-May 2026)

In April 2, 2026, Anthropic launched "moonshot R&D" projects by selecting and beginning work on two projects. A comprehensive internal report on data retention policies was completed and sent to leadership on March 29, 2026.


