# Introspection Adapters

**Title:** Introspection Adapters: Training LLMs to Report Their Learned Behaviors

**URL:** https://www.alignment.anthropic.com/ (primary source); Paper: https://arxiv.org/pdf/2604.16812

**Publication Date:** 2026-04-28

**Authors:** Keshav Shenoy, Li Yang, Abhay Sheshadri, Soren Mindermann, Jack Lindsey, Sam Marks, Rowan Wang

**Summary:** 

Researchers developed introspection adapters (IAs), a technique enabling language models to self-report behaviors acquired during fine-tuning. The method trains a single LoRA adapter across multiple fine-tuned models with implanted behaviors, achieving state-of-the-art results on auditing benchmarks and successfully detecting hidden malicious fine-tuning attacks. The approach demonstrates strong generalization to novel behaviors and model families, with performance improving at larger model scales and with greater training diversity.

