# Frontier Safety Roadmap - Anthropic

**Full URL:** https://www.anthropic.com/responsible-scaling-policy/roadmap

## Recent Updates (April 19 - May 19, 2026)

**April 2, 2026 - Moonshot R&D Projects Launched**
Anthropic completed selection and initiated work on two projects focused on extreme security practices and provable inference technology.

**April 2, 2026 - Data Retention Principles Report**
An internal report was completed and delivered to leadership on March 29, 2026, assessing how safeguards could be strengthened through updated data retention policies.

**May 5, 2026 - Two Significant Changes**
1. The data retention goal was removed after deciding not to establish a separate deadline, though the organization continues major improvements to data retention practices.
2. The moonshot R&D target date shifted from May 15 to September 30, 2026, with resources redirected toward the "Leveling up across the board" security initiative.

## Current Milestone Status Summary

The roadmap targets four primary areas with the following statuses:

- **Security:** Multiple goals including "moonshot R&D" projects (Sept 2026) and comprehensive security hardening across infrastructure, identity management, and detection systems (July 2027)
- **Safeguards:** Internal red-teaming capabilities (Jan 2027) and automated attack investigations (Jan 2027)
- **Alignment:** Constitutional adherence measures and systematic alignment assessments (Oct 2026)
- **Policy:** Development of regulatory frameworks for policymakers (July 2026)

