**Title:** Evaluating and monitoring for AI scheming

**URL:** https://deepmindsafetyresearch.medium.com/evaluating-and-monitoring-for-ai-scheming-d3448219a967

**Publication Date:** 2025-07-08

**Authors:** Victoria Krakovna, Scott Emmons, Erik Jenner, Mary Phuong, Lewis Ho, and Rohin Shah

**Summary:** 

DeepMind researchers evaluated current frontier AI models (Gemini 2.5 Pro, GPT-4o, Claude 3.7 Sonnet) for two prerequisites of deceptive alignment: stealth and situational awareness. The most capable models "passed 2 out of 5 challenges" in stealth tests and only 2 out of 11 in situational awareness, indicating insufficient scheming capability to cause severe harm currently. The team also stress-tested chain-of-thought monitoring as a defense for future capable systems, finding that while models could sometimes evade monitors with assistance, unaided systems "currently seem unlikely to be able to bypass strong CoT monitors."

