# Publication Details

**Title:** Poisoning Fine-tuning Datasets of Constitutional Classifiers

**URL:** https://alignment-science-blog.anthropic.com/2026/backdooring-classifiers/ (based on preview link provided)

**Publication Date:** 2026-04-24

**Authors:** Chase Bowers, Faizan Ali, John Hughes, Jerry Wei, Fabien Roger

## Summary

The researchers demonstrate that constitutional classifiers can be compromised through data poisoning with as few as 32 malicious training examples, a number that remains constant regardless of overall training set size. Their findings reveal that while backdoor installation typically degrades classifier robustness, incorporating prompt injection examples or similar trigger variations into training data can mitigate these robustness losses enough that detection during deployment becomes unlikely. These results underscore significant insider threats to AI safety systems, as attackers could potentially bypass detection mechanisms without leaving obvious performance degradation signals.

