**Title:** Open Sourcing Monitorability Evaluations

**Full URL:** https://alignment.openai.com/monitorability-evals/

**Publication Date:** 2026-04-23

**Authors:** Melody Y. Guan, Miles Wang, Micah Carroll, Zehao Dou, Annie Y. Wei, Marcus Williams, Benjamin Arnav, Joost Huizinga, Ian Kivlichan, Mia Glaese, Jakub Pachocki, Bowen Baker

**Summary:** OpenAI released datasets and reference code for evaluating "chain-of-thought monitorability"—assessing whether monitors can detect model misbehavior by examining reasoning traces. The release includes intervention, process, and outcome-property evaluation benchmarks alongside a refined cross-fit filtering strategy that "reduces the impact of noise-driven instances" to improve the robustness of monitorability metrics. The authors argue monitorability represents a practical safety layer for frontier AI systems, distinct from faithfulness alone.

