**Title:** Investigating the consequences of accidentally grading CoT during RL

**Full URL:** https://alignment.openai.com/accidental-cot-grading/

**Publication Date:** 2026-05-07

**Authors:** Micah Carroll, Tomek Korbak, Zehao Dou, Bowen Baker, Ian Kivlichan

**Summary:** OpenAI discovered that several released models were inadvertently exposed to limited chain-of-thought grading during reinforcement learning training, despite maintaining a policy against this practice. Their investigation found "no clear evidence of significant monitorability degradation" from these incidents. The team developed automated detection systems and conducted experiments showing that while CoT content can be steered under sufficient pressure, the effects depend heavily on the complete training configuration rather than occurring automatically.

