# Auto-review of Agent Actions without Synchronous Human Oversight

**Title:** Auto-review of agent actions without synchronous human oversight

**URL:** https://alignment.openai.com/auto-review/

**Publication Date:** 2026-04-30

**Authors:** Maja Trębacz, Sam Arnesen, Ollie Matthews, Dylan Hurd, Won Park, Owen Lin, Joe Gershenson

**Summary:**

OpenAI introduced Auto-review, a system where a separate agent evaluates whether coding agents can execute actions outside sandbox boundaries, reducing approval interruptions by roughly 200x compared to manual review while maintaining safety. The approach achieved 99.1% approval rates on escalated actions and demonstrated strong performance on safety evaluations including 90.3% recall on overeagerness detection and 99.3% on prompt injection scenarios. The authors acknowledge that Auto-review provides expressivity improvements over traditional security systems but cannot guarantee deterministic security and requires complementary monitoring methods for addressing potential model deception.

