**Title:** Research Sabotage in ML Codebases

**URL:** https://substack.com/@ericgan3 (article appears to be on Redwood Research blog)

**Date:** 2026-04-29

**Author(s):** Eric Gan

**Summary:**

This research introduces Auditing Sabotage Bench, a benchmark containing 9 ML research codebases with intentionally sabotaged variants, designed to evaluate how well auditors can detect covert modifications to research. Testing frontier LLMs and human auditors revealed that "neither reliably catches sabotage," with the best performer (Gemini 3.1 Pro) achieving only 42% accuracy at identifying the primary sabotage and an AUROC of 0.77. The study found that design-based sabotages—particularly omissions of crucial implementation details—proved substantially harder to detect than logic errors, and that LLM-generated sabotages could partially evade detection by similarly capable monitoring systems.

