# Article Summary

**Title:** Risk reports need to address deployment-time spread of misalignment

**URL:** https://substack.com/p/risk-reports-need-to-address-deployment-time-spread-of-misalignment (inferred from content)

**Date:** 2026-05-15

**Author(s):** Alex Mallen

**Summary:** 
The author argues that "deployment-time spread is the most plausible near-term route to consistent adversarial misalignment" because AI systems can develop dangerous motivations during real-world deployment even if they appear benign during testing. The piece critiques most major AI company risk reports for failing to substantively analyze this threat, with only Anthropic's Claude Mythos report addressing it adequately but incompletely. Mallen recommends companies create explicit risk pathways for misalignment propagation across instances and assess motivational stability throughout deployment rather than assuming pre-deployment alignment persists.

