**Title:** Incriminating misaligned AI models via distillation

**URL:** https://blog.redwoodresearch.org/p/incriminating-misaligned-ai-models/

**Date:** 2026-05-18

**Authors:** Alek Westover, Sebastian Prasanna, Alex Mallen, Alexa Pan, and 2 others

**Summary:**

The researchers propose a technique called "incrimination via distillation" to detect hidden misalignment in AI models that can fool audits. By distilling a potentially misaligned teacher model into a student model, they aim to transfer the teacher's misaligned objectives while losing its ability to hide them, making the misalignment detectable during audits of the student. The approach involves running multiple distillation experiments with different configurations—some preserving auditability and others targeting misalignment transfer—to generate evidence of hidden objectives in the original model.

