# MirrorCode Report Summary

**Title:** MirrorCode: Evidence that AI can already do some weeks-long coding tasks

**URL:** https://epoch.ai/blog/mirrorcode-preliminary-results

**Publication Date:** 2026-04-10

**Authors:** Tom Adamczewski, David Rein, David Owen, Florian Brand

**Summary:**

The MirrorCode benchmark demonstrates that Claude Opus 4.6 can autonomously reimplement complex software without source code access—successfully recreating a 16,000-line bioinformatics toolkit that human engineers estimate would require 2–17 weeks. The research reveals sustained progress with inference scaling on larger projects and identifies key improvements in newer models, including better persistence in task completion and superior architectural choices. While results are significant for autonomous software engineering capabilities, important limitations include reliance on precise specifications and unresolved questions about memorization's influence on performance.

