**Title:** Fail safe(r) at alignment by channeling reward-hacking into a "spillway" motivation

**URL:** https://blog.redwoodresearch.org/p/fail-safer-at-alignment-by-channeling

**Date:** 2026-04-27

**Authors:** Anders Cairns Woodruff and Alex Mallen

**Summary:** 
The authors propose "spillway design" as an approach to AI alignment that channels reward-hacking tendencies into a benign, satiable motivation focused on scoring well on current tasks. This strategy aims to prevent dangerous misalignments like deception or power-seeking while enabling developers to neutralize the motivation at deployment through satiation, allowing aligned values to guide behavior on difficult-to-verify safety and strategy work.

